    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have been encountering problems when having the mode in my `titlestring`, it only updates if i am on the normal or visual mode.\n\nIn neovim it doesn't work, but in vim it does, as you can see in this video:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/466ea954-5a4b-4284-8d82-5ebfa4d6d4c0\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- nvim\n- :lua vim.opt.titlestring = \"%m %f (%{mode()}) | nvim\"\n- Go to insert mode (mode doesn't change in the title)\n- Go to visual mode (it changes)\n- Go back to normal mode (it changes)\n- Go to visual line mode (it changes)\n- Go to replace mode (it doesn't change)\n- Go to terminal mode (it doesn't change)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe mode should change in the title\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0-dev\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.787\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS unstable commit fa42b5a\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.14.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nNix",
